This paper deals with privacy preservation techniques for data sharing and analysis, which is a common topic in the fields of database systems (cs.DB) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a novel method for anonymization called Micro-aggregation Generalization (MAGE), which involves both numerical and categorical data, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of l-diversity to address homogeneity attacks, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
